//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a paired set of artifacts sharing a common
{rbtga_consecration}
but distinguished by suffix.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(`-image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(`-about`) contains build provenance, SBOM, and metadata.
Abjuring an ark removes both artifacts as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_CONSECRATION»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if vessel missing: "Vessel parameter required"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if consecration missing: "Consecration parameter required"

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtga_consecration}
. *Validate Consecration Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_CONSECRATION»` matches pattern `YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ` or similar timestamp format
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Consecration format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Registry Endpoint*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_HOST»` as `{rbrr_gcp_region}-docker.pkg.dev`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_PATH»` as `{rbrr_depot_project_id}/{rbrr_gar_repository}`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_BASE»` as `https://«REGISTRY_HOST»/v2/«REGISTRY_PATH»`

//axhos_step
. *Construct Ark Tags*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-image`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ABOUT_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-about`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Ark Existence*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#pulling-manifests[Docker Registry API: HEAD manifests] for `«IMAGE_TAG»`:
... method: `HEAD`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-image`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... header: `Accept: application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json, application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json, application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json, application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404
.. {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request for `«ABOUT_TAG»`:
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-about`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ABOUT_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404

//axhos_step
. *Evaluate Ark State*:
.. If both `«IMAGE_EXISTS»` and `«ABOUT_EXISTS»` are false:
... {rbbc_fatal}
"Ark not found: neither -image nor -about exists"
.. If exactly one exists:
... {rbbc_warn}
"Orphaned artifact detected"
... {rbbc_show}
which artifact exists and which is missing
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARTIFACTS_TO_DELETE»` as list of existing artifacts

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. Unless `--force` flag provided:
... {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure ark «INPUT_VESSEL»/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»:" followed by each artifact in `«ARTIFACTS_TO_DELETE»`
... {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
... {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Image Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«IMAGE_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-image`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -image artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete About Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«ABOUT_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-about`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -about artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoo_output_of_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Ark abjured: «INPUT_VESSEL»/«INPUT_CONSECRATION»"
.. For each deleted artifact:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «TAG» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when all existing ark artifacts have been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_beseech}

NOTE: This operation petitions
{rbtgi_repository}
to reveal its consecrated
{rbtga_ark}s,
correlating
{rbtga_ark_image}
and
{rbtga_ark_about}
artifacts by shared
{rbtga_consecration}
timestamp.

The
{rbtr_director}
beseeches the registry:

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Accept Optional Vessel Filter*:
.. If `«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument, restrict enumeration to that vessel
.. If omitted, enumerate all vessels

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages*:
.. {rbbc_call}
Google Artifact Registry API to fetch all packages from
{rbtgi_repository}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PACKAGES»` as list of package names
.. If `«INPUT_VESSEL»` specified, filter to matching package only

//axhos_step
. *Fetch Tags Per Package*:
.. For each package in `«PACKAGES»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry HTTP API V2 tag list endpoint
... For each tag returned, classify by suffix:
.... Tags ending in `-image` → ark image artifact
.... Tags ending in `-about` → ark about artifact
.... Other tags → skip (plain image tags, not ark artifacts)
... {rbbc_store}
consecration base by stripping suffix from ark tags

//axhos_step
. *Correlate Ark Pairs*:
.. Group artifacts by vessel + consecration
.. Track presence of each artifact type per group
.. {rbbc_store}
correlation results showing which artifacts exist for each ark

//axhoo_output_of_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Present Tabular Results*:
.. Sort by vessel (alphabetically), then by consecration (newest first within vessel)
.. {rbbc_show}
header row: `VESSEL`, `CONSECRATION`, `-image`, `-about`
.. For each ark (unique vessel+consecration pair):
... {rbbc_show}
vessel name, consecration timestamp
... {rbbc_show}
`✓` for present artifacts, `✗` for absent artifacts
.. Display reveals orphaned arks (only one artifact present) and complete arks (both artifacts)

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when all arks have been enumerated and the tabular display presents the correlation state of each consecration's artifact pair.
The beseech reveals the registry's ark inventory without modifying any resources.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}

NOTE: This operation conjures an
{rbtga_ark}
in
{rbtgi_repository}
by building a container image from a vessel specification and assembling build provenance metadata. The
{rbtr_director}
performs the build via
{gcb_service}.

NOTE: This is the ark-level view of the build operation. For detailed build procedure steps, see
{rbtgo_trigger_build}.

The conjure operation:

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel directory provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel contains conjuring configuration (RBRV_CONJURE_DOCKERFILE, RBRV_CONJURE_BLDCONTEXT)

//axhos_step
. *Execute Build*:
.. Delegate to
{rbtgo_trigger_build}
which dispatches via the vessel's
{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
.. All build parameters baked in
{rbtgr_build_json}
— zero custom substitution overrides
.. Waits for build completion
.. On success, both
{rbtga_ark_image}
and
{rbtga_ark_about}
artifacts are created with shared
{rbtga_consecration}
.. {rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed attestation on the built image

//axhoo_output_of_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
vessel image built with consecration tag

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates a complete
{rbtga_ark}
with both image and about artifacts sharing the same
{rbtga_consecration}.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_summon}

NOTE: This operation summons an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository},
pulling both
{rbtga_ark_image}
and
{rbtga_ark_about}
artifacts to the local container runtime. Uses
{rbtr_retriever}
credentials when available, falling back to
{rbtr_director}.

NOTE: This is the ark-level view of image retrieval. For single-artifact retrieval, see
{rbtgo_image_retrieve}.

The summon operation:

//axhop_parameter_from_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
consecration provided as second argument

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_retriever}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_retriever_authenticate}
.. Fall back to
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
if retriever credentials unavailable
.. {rbbc_store}
authentication token for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Ark Tags*:
.. {rbbc_store}
image tag as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-image`
.. {rbbc_store}
about tag as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_CONSECRATION»-about`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Ark Existence*:
.. {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API HEAD requests for both artifacts
.. {rbbc_store}
image existence status
.. {rbbc_store}
about existence status

//axhos_step
. *Evaluate Ark State*:
.. If both artifacts missing:
... {rbbc_fatal}
"Ark not found"
.. If exactly one missing:
... {rbbc_warn}
"Orphaned artifact detected"

//axhos_step
. *Docker Login and Pull*:
.. {rbbc_call}
docker login to registry
.. For each existing artifact:
... {rbbc_call}
docker pull to retrieve artifact to local container runtime

//axhoo_output_of_type
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
which artifacts were retrieved

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution retrieves the {rbtga_ark} artifacts to the local container runtime, making them available for use.
